          Huntsville is a city built on precision. The engineers who designed
          the Saturn V, the defense analysts who safeguard national security,
          the biotech researchers pioneering tomorrow's medicine—these are
          people who solve problems for a living. And yet, the most analytical
          minds in North Alabama routinely make the same mistake with their own
          homes: they wait. They wait until the drywall crack becomes a visible
          scar across the living room ceiling. They wait until the exterior
          paint has checked and crazed beyond spot repair. They wait until the
          gutter system has deposited enough debris to compromise the fascia
          board behind it.
        </p>
