          deferred maintenance on a missile defense system somehow accept it in
          the structures where their families sleep. This is not a judgment—it
          is a recognition of how busy Huntsville lives actually are. When you
          commute to Redstone Arsenal, manage classified programs, or pull
          twelve-hour shifts at Huntsville Hospital, the baseboards in the guest
          bathroom do not exactly command your attention. We understand that. It
