          The antebellum mansions of Twickenham require period-appropriate
          restoration techniques that most modern contractors cannot execute.
          The mid-century ranches of Jones Valley need systems-level
          updating—insulation, weatherstripping, window seals—that address
          decades of thermal cycling in Alabama's four-season climate. The newer
          luxury homes of Hampton Cove, built to high standards, still develop
          settling cracks, require gutter maintenance as the surrounding
          landscape matures, and need the kind of trim touch-ups that separate a
          well-maintained residence from one that merely looks new from the
          street.
        </p>
