          Elevation changes create drainage complexities. Dense tree cover
          produces aggressive gutter clogging and creates conditions for
          moisture-related wood deterioration that lowland neighborhoods rarely
          encounter. If your home sits on the mountain, you need a contractor
          who has worked on the mountain—not one who is guessing about slope,
          runoff, and canopy-related moisture.
        </p>
        <p>
